(2) Opera-Related Enterprises Rise Annually, but the Influx Slows Post-Pandemic

In 2016, the Ministry of Culture issued a directive to further step up support for grassroots opera troupes. Driven by this, 2017 witnessed a staggering 83.75% growth rate in opera-related enterprises, nearly doubling the quantity of 2016. However, hit by the pandemic after 2020, although numbers continued to crawl upward, the net growth dropped drastically and never broke the 1,000 mark again.

