Livestreaming Platforms Pave New Horizons for Traditional Opera Staging
Li Shujian, Dean of the Henan Yu Opera House, once reflected that modern opera performances suffer from a structural imbalance: "There are plenty of elderly viewers but too few young faces; plenty of rural tours but too few urban bookings; plenty of corporate chartered audiences but too few individual ticket buyers. This is a universal crisis across the entire industry. Opera desperately needs young talent, but it needs a young audience even more. Art is meant to be seen; if no one watches, the opera vanishes."

Nevertheless, on the Douyin platform, we witness the rebirth of traditional opera. By rebranding livestreaming virtual gifts as "the new theater tickets," the purchasing power of young audiences cannot be underestimated. By treating the digital livestreaming room as "the new stage," grassroots performers are carving out a vast and boundless territory.

